1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:02,040
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:03,780
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,010 --> 00:00:06,010
(Episode 47)

4
00:00:06,010 --> 00:00:07,150
I'm going to walk away.

5
00:00:09,950 --> 00:00:12,950
Listen carefully, Gong Ju Ah.
If you let me go now,

6
00:00:15,350 --> 00:00:16,620
we're really over.

7
00:00:42,650 --> 00:00:43,680
Don't go.

8
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:45,980
Don't go, Yang Hyun Bin.

9
00:00:47,450 --> 00:00:49,450
Don't turn your back on me.

10
00:01:17,420 --> 00:01:18,620
Gosh.

11
00:01:20,190 --> 00:01:22,190
What's taking those two so long?

12
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:27,030
- Are they fighting again?
- Again? Did they fight often?

13
00:01:27,160 --> 00:01:30,900
- Often? More like every day.
- Gosh, it was so awkward.

14
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:33,930
They were at each other's throats
any chance they got.

15
00:01:34,570 --> 00:01:35,700
Really?

16
00:01:36,070 --> 00:01:37,700
Gosh,
since they were always together,

17
00:01:37,770 --> 00:01:39,240
I thought a romance might blossom.

18
00:01:39,370 --> 00:01:42,310
Romance? More like a thriller.

19
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:48,150
By any chance...

20
00:01:48,810 --> 00:01:50,820
- Interested in marrying Hyun Bin?
- Excuse me?

21
00:01:50,850 --> 00:01:51,880
Mother!

22
00:01:56,820 --> 00:01:58,360
I really got ahead of myself.

23
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:01,560
Have you talked to Hyun Bin
about it?

24
00:02:02,730 --> 00:02:03,730
Father.

25
00:02:04,060 --> 00:02:06,800
At this rate,
Hyun Bin is going to disown me.

26
00:02:06,870 --> 00:02:09,530
Be prepared for that,
and push forward.

27
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:12,300
Father.

28
00:02:13,570 --> 00:02:15,340
If you can't, I will.

29
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:17,710
No, wait...

30
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:21,950
Why is he suddenly being like this?

31
00:02:25,150 --> 00:02:26,480
But this is strange.

32
00:02:30,290 --> 00:02:34,630
See? You still liked me
even after we broke up.

33
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:38,130
Look who's talking. You said
you had no personal feelings.

34
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,400
You kept being so touchy.

35
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:41,800
I should have known
when you kissed me as a dare.

36
00:02:42,570 --> 00:02:44,500
So what now? Want to start over?

37
00:02:48,070 --> 00:02:51,140
You told me not to go.
Not to turn my back on you.

38
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,850
No, that's different.

39
00:02:55,780 --> 00:02:58,880
So you have feelings for me
but no confidence?

40
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:03,820
It's just that nothing has changed
since we broke up.

41
00:03:03,990 --> 00:03:06,560
But the feud between our families
is over.

42
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:08,330
Instead,
our families became in-laws.

43
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,370
Do you even love me?

44
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:17,840
Why all of a sudden?

45
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,270
You can't answer, can you?

46
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:26,410
Honestly, I don't know
if I have the right to say it.

47
00:03:27,310 --> 00:03:30,520
Because I don't know
what we are anymore.

48
00:03:31,550 --> 00:03:32,680
Then think about it.

49
00:03:33,550 --> 00:03:36,690
Think about what our relationship
should be from now on,

50
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,560
and let's talk tomorrow
when we're sober.

51
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:42,090
- Tomorrow?
- Why? Do you need more time?

52
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:45,830
No, that's fine. Tomorrow.
We'll talk tomorrow.

53
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:54,410
- She should really tone it down.
- I'm home.

54
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:55,470
- Yes.
- You're back.

55
00:03:55,540 --> 00:03:57,110
You're back?
You're pretty late today.

56
00:03:57,780 --> 00:04:00,780
- We had a dinner at my aunt's.
- I see.

57
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:03,550
Ju Ah, I heard you're going back
to work at Taehan?

58
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:07,320
Yes, the brand I launched
got absorbed into Taehan Fashion.

59
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:09,290
Hey, Gong Ju Ah.

60
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:12,690
You aren't, by any chance,
seeing Director Yang again, are you?

61
00:04:13,790 --> 00:04:15,760
No, Dad.

62
00:04:16,090 --> 00:04:17,330
Who's Director Yang?

63
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,560
The grandson
from the herbal medicine clinic.

64
00:04:19,630 --> 00:04:21,330
Remember,
we saw him at the hospital.

65
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:24,240
- Seon Chul's grandson?
- Yes.

66
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,840
She was dating him?

67
00:04:27,770 --> 00:04:31,710
- We almost had double in-laws.
- Well, that is...

68
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:34,410
- They broke up before that, Father.
- Right.

69
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:36,780
That's a relief.

70
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:40,550
- I'm going to head upstairs, then.
- Okay, sure.

71
00:04:42,950 --> 00:04:44,860
- Turn it on.
- Okay.

72
00:04:48,130 --> 00:04:51,130
To Stylist Yang,

73
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:55,400
who has finally made a name
for herself.

74
00:04:55,470 --> 00:04:57,800
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

75
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:01,340
Are you that happy just because
the CEO said your name?

76
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,810
Her saying my name...

77
00:05:07,210 --> 00:05:10,920
wasn't just part of the process.
It was the result.

78
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,920
Until then,

79
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:16,690
I was a complete nobody.

80
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:20,830
Just like Yang Eun Bin
to Gong Woo Jae.

81
00:05:21,890 --> 00:05:24,630
Hey, what do you mean
you're a nobody to me?

82
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:27,570
I said "before." In the past.

83
00:05:28,130 --> 00:05:32,140
Anyway, for someone like me
who felt invisible,

84
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:37,980
to become someone who is wanted...

85
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:40,450
is such a special thing, is it not?

86
00:05:42,180 --> 00:05:44,280
Like Yang Eun Bin to Gong Woo Jae?

87
00:05:45,180 --> 00:05:46,180
Me?

88
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:48,790
What are you talking about?

89
00:05:49,990 --> 00:05:51,490
If you don't get it, never mind.

90
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:55,860
- Then let's toast again.
- Cheers.

91
00:05:57,430 --> 00:05:59,430
But I knew you could do it.

92
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:01,830
Ever since you were a kid,
once you set your mind to something,

93
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:02,900
you always saw it through.

94
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:04,800
Remember in elementary school,
when you tried...

95
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:06,970
to collect all the stickers
from that character bread?

96
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:09,340
Do you remember eating
only that bread for months?

97
00:06:10,980 --> 00:06:13,080
To be honest,

98
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:16,410
I was not collecting the stickers.

99
00:06:17,050 --> 00:06:21,490
- What?
- Since you were collecting, I did.

100
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:23,620
Why?

101
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:26,360
I was creating something
to talk about.

102
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:31,160
So you would say
at least one more word to me.

103
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:32,960
I...

104
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:36,500
I really liked you a lot.

105
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,210
Not anymore?

106
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:53,680
What?

107
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:56,550
Of course not.

108
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,520
Not anymore.

109
00:06:59,390 --> 00:07:00,460
What should I do?

110
00:07:01,930 --> 00:07:03,960
I have only just started
to like you.

111
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,570
What did you say?

112
00:07:11,570 --> 00:07:13,440
I said I have only just started
to like you.

113
00:07:19,340 --> 00:07:21,910
I am sorry. Am I too late?

114
00:07:30,150 --> 00:07:31,890
I am kidding.

115
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:34,830
- You were so surprised.
- Gosh.

116
00:07:35,390 --> 00:07:38,430
What? I cannot believe
I did not know it was a joke.

117
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:41,730
How embarrassing. Gosh.

118
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,400
Well...

119
00:07:47,670 --> 00:07:51,110
Our CEO is going on an overseas
business trip,

120
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:56,080
and she asked me if I had
a passport. I was so thrilled.

121
00:07:56,150 --> 00:07:57,150
Hey.

122
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:03,050
I mean, how did she know
I just renewed it?

123
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:05,560
Is she going to take me with her?

124
00:08:06,890 --> 00:08:07,890
Hey.

125
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:12,500
- You scared me. What a surprise.
- Hey, Min Ji Hu.

126
00:08:12,830 --> 00:08:14,000
You have been drinking.

127
00:08:14,070 --> 00:08:17,970
Yes, it was my treat.

128
00:08:20,740 --> 00:08:23,170
Since Ji Hu is here,
I will get going.

129
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:26,010
Yes, you should go. Get out of here.

130
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:28,810
I will go. I am going.
You do not have to tell me to go.

131
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:32,920
Okay, get home safe, Woo Jae.

132
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:36,020
- Hey. Let's go inside.
- Hey.

133
00:08:36,090 --> 00:08:37,890
- What?
- Do you still like Woo Jae?

134
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:41,730
- Hey, of course not.
- Then stop hanging out with him.

135
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:44,260
He likes you.

136
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:50,200
What does a little kid
like you know?

137
00:08:50,270 --> 00:08:53,340
Hey, you do not know anything.

138
00:08:53,910 --> 00:08:56,810
We are just in-laws.

139
00:08:57,110 --> 00:08:58,110
Is that so?

140
00:08:58,340 --> 00:09:00,410
You are the one
who does not know anything.

141
00:09:02,210 --> 00:09:03,210
Wow.

142
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:06,880
Outstanding store owner
Cha Se Ri. What?

143
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:11,320
Wow, how is Se Ri so capable
at everything she does?

144
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:13,020
Oh, stop it, you.

145
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:16,260
Right, what happened with
Councilor Hwang?

146
00:09:16,690 --> 00:09:17,860
That?

147
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:21,700
He said he is giving up
the nomination.

148
00:09:23,070 --> 00:09:24,270
I am sorry, Se Ri.

149
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:27,870
No. You did well.

150
00:09:28,310 --> 00:09:31,640
Really?
Did I really do the right thing?

151
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:34,480
Honestly,
I was getting sick and tired of...

152
00:09:34,550 --> 00:09:36,880
having to please
Councilor Hwang's wife.

153
00:09:36,950 --> 00:09:41,720
Gosh, you went through so much.
I am sorry.

154
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:46,990
You are the one who had it rough.
Anyway, honey. About your father...

155
00:09:47,260 --> 00:09:49,990
I mean, why is he suddenly
pushing us so hard?

156
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:54,000
After Mom passed away
the way she did,

157
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:55,870
I think it might be guilt.

158
00:09:55,930 --> 00:09:57,700
He probably feels
he has to do better...

159
00:09:57,770 --> 00:09:59,000
by his remaining children.

160
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:01,670
I think he's stressed
about that, too.

161
00:10:01,740 --> 00:10:04,140
I know, but still,

162
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:07,580
him pushing us
to get Yang Hyun Bin married...

163
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:09,180
it's just so exhausting.

164
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,820
Can't he marry Jeong Han's daughter?

165
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:12,820
Honey.

166
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:15,320
No, I mean, honestly,
becoming double in-laws,

167
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:17,920
it's not that big of a deal
nowadays.

168
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:21,360
I'm sure I can convince Father.
Right?

169
00:10:21,430 --> 00:10:22,560
No, I can't do it. I can't.

170
00:10:22,660 --> 00:10:24,530
Didn't you see
at the formal family meeting,

171
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:26,430
how she looked me right in the eye
and talked back to me.

172
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:29,070
Come on,
she had good reason to back then.

173
00:10:29,130 --> 00:10:31,970
Fine. Okay.
I know I was in the wrong,

174
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:34,410
so I'd understand
if other people did it.

175
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:36,610
Like Dr. Han Seong Mi
or your sister.

176
00:10:36,670 --> 00:10:38,880
If Ms. Na had done it,
I'd honestly be fine.

177
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:42,650
But Gong Ju Ah, she has no right
to treat me like that.

178
00:10:42,710 --> 00:10:45,580
No matter if they broke up,
I'm her ex-boyfriend's mother.

179
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:48,990
- I guess so?
- Honestly, no one in our family...

180
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:51,320
knew they were dating
until they broke up.

181
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:53,190
But our Yang Hyun Bin went over
to their house...

182
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:55,330
and it seems he did all he could
to get their blessing.

183
00:10:55,830 --> 00:10:58,200
It looked like only our
Yang Hyun Bin was madly in love,

184
00:10:58,260 --> 00:11:02,430
- and that made me even more upset.
- That's true, isn't it?

185
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:13,080
Do you even love me?

186
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:15,810
You can't answer, can you?

187
00:11:16,810 --> 00:11:20,050
Why couldn't I answer him?

188
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:32,630
Wait, you want to go back
to being a doctor?

189
00:11:33,930 --> 00:11:34,930
Yes.

190
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:38,270
Why? You don't think I can do it?
I can.

191
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:40,140
Who said you couldn't?

192
00:11:40,370 --> 00:11:43,540
But isn't your medical license
suspended?

193
00:11:43,610 --> 00:11:45,380
I'll have to go to
the Medical Association.

194
00:11:48,410 --> 00:11:51,480
Why?
Did you remember something again?

195
00:11:51,850 --> 00:11:54,650
No. You were always
tripping over stones...

196
00:11:54,690 --> 00:11:55,920
and about to fall.

197
00:11:57,620 --> 00:12:01,260
Right.
You'd tell me to watch my step,

198
00:12:01,330 --> 00:12:03,030
and you'd nag me so much about it.

199
00:12:03,090 --> 00:12:07,530
So don't just look ahead.
Watch where you're walking.

200
00:12:08,830 --> 00:12:11,470
It was nice you lost your memory
and stopped nagging.

201
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:13,140
I guess the good old days are over.

202
00:12:13,570 --> 00:12:14,940
Take my hand.

203
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,480
What's this?

204
00:12:26,850 --> 00:12:29,250
You're running for city council
as an independent?

205
00:12:29,490 --> 00:12:30,490
Yes.

206
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:32,990
The idea of
tearing down Onjeong Market...

207
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:35,090
was something
I just couldn't stand for.

208
00:12:36,690 --> 00:12:38,000
And you think you can win?

209
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:39,560
I have to try.

210
00:12:40,530 --> 00:12:43,270
- Jeong Han agreed to help.
- Do your best.

211
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:47,000
- You have to win this election.
- Yes, Father.

212
00:12:52,340 --> 00:12:55,880
Sweetie.
A lady shouldn't eat like that.

213
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:58,020
Yes, she can. You should try eating
like this too, Mom.

214
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,150
Goodness, so unrefined.

215
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:01,350
I was in a beauty pageant, you know.

216
00:13:01,950 --> 00:13:05,920
- Pageant contestants aren't people.
- Why you little...

217
00:13:05,990 --> 00:13:06,990
That's right.

218
00:13:07,060 --> 00:13:10,390
You're always watching your figure,
eating like a bird,

219
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:13,560
- that's why you're always anemic.
- All right.

220
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:14,900
By the way,
who were you drinking with...

221
00:13:14,970 --> 00:13:16,070
that you came home
so late last night?

222
00:13:16,270 --> 00:13:17,800
It was a work dinner.

223
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:23,540
But Grandfather, what's wrong with
being double in-laws?

224
00:13:23,610 --> 00:13:25,610
I heard
there's no legal issue with it.

225
00:13:25,810 --> 00:13:28,010
What do you mean,
"what's wrong with it?"

226
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:31,580
Think how tangled
the family tree would get.

227
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:34,720
How will our ancestors even receive
their proper memorial rites?

228
00:13:35,420 --> 00:13:37,660
How could I face our ancestors
in the afterlife?

229
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:42,660
My goodness, Father.
Why do you keep talking about dying?

230
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:47,130
Father, are you feeling unwell?

231
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:50,600
It's nothing. Just eat.

232
00:13:59,410 --> 00:14:02,050
So, you're really running
as an independent?

233
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:07,120
Yes. Father said we should do
what you suggested.

234
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:08,390
What I suggested?

235
00:14:09,150 --> 00:14:11,790
But our brilliant daughter-in-law
said it herself.

236
00:14:11,860 --> 00:14:16,230
We didn't believe in rumors.
We believed in people.

237
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:19,500
But if we start hating people now
and get rid of the market,

238
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:23,400
it won't be Jo Mi Hyang
who took 30 years from us.

239
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:26,400
We will have lost who we are.

240
00:14:27,470 --> 00:14:30,070
- Did he really say that?
- He really did.

241
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:32,710
Dae Han and I got persuaded
just like that.

242
00:14:32,710 --> 00:14:35,050
When Yang Dong Ik heard that,

243
00:14:35,110 --> 00:14:37,580
he became determined
to run as an independent.

244
00:14:38,580 --> 00:14:41,750
It's great having Father around.

245
00:14:44,620 --> 00:14:48,660
Goodness, why do the women here
hide when they struggle?

246
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:50,390
Oh, is that so?

247
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:51,730
I'm telling you.

248
00:14:51,730 --> 00:14:54,330
You and your mother-in-law
are both the same,

249
00:14:54,430 --> 00:14:57,000
always acting so tough.

250
00:14:57,740 --> 00:15:01,070
- Honey.
- Yes?

251
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:02,610
It's just...

252
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:06,710
Where I had my radiation therapy,
it stings a lot.

253
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:09,110
- Could you take a look?
- Really?

254
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:13,680
Let me see.

255
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:18,190
What is this? My goodness.

256
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:20,760
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

257
00:15:21,230 --> 00:15:25,400
I know. I don't know why I keep
hiding things from you.

258
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:26,700
This must have stung so much,

259
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,570
even with your clothes
brushing against it.

260
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:31,800
Why didn't you tell me sooner?
Come on,

261
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:33,040
let's get you to the hospital
right away.

262
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:35,140
I'll dress the wound for you.

263
00:15:35,940 --> 00:15:39,810
- Nice. Should've done this sooner.
- I know.

264
00:15:40,980 --> 00:15:44,210
- Come on.
- You silly. Honestly.

265
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:46,050
It's all right.

266
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:51,560
What was that?

267
00:16:46,580 --> 00:16:49,180
- You did well.
- Mom, Father, it's time to eat.

268
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:50,250
Okay.

269
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,580
Wow, this looks delicious.

270
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:53,980
Yes, please have a seat.

271
00:16:54,990 --> 00:16:57,720
Honey, you should sit here today.

272
00:16:58,190 --> 00:16:59,190
Me?

273
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:02,660
- This was always your seat.
- Was it?

274
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,900
Mom, that was your seat
for 30 years.

275
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:07,830
Are you giving your seat to Father?

276
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:09,270
I want to now.

277
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:10,930
Well then, shall I?

278
00:17:20,010 --> 00:17:22,480
Didn't this used to be
a low table we sat at,

279
00:17:22,550 --> 00:17:24,080
not a dining table like this?

280
00:17:24,420 --> 00:17:27,720
- Do you remember, Father?
- I remember it vaguely.

281
00:17:28,220 --> 00:17:30,490
Yes. We replaced it with this table
not long ago.

282
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:32,760
And we also got a bed
for Mother's room.

283
00:17:32,820 --> 00:17:34,120
I see.

284
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:38,000
- Why'd you get such a small one?
- Pardon?

285
00:17:38,630 --> 00:17:39,630
Well...

286
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:43,230
Well, since you sleep on the floor,
isn’t it uncomfortable?

287
00:17:43,670 --> 00:17:45,070
There's that,

288
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:47,540
but sleeping separately
doesn't feel right, does it?

289
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:51,540
Father, we'll get a bigger one.

290
00:17:52,010 --> 00:17:54,910
- Let's do that.
- Of course. Of course we should.

291
00:17:54,980 --> 00:17:55,980
Yes, we should.

292
00:17:56,050 --> 00:17:58,980
I guess Father wants to sleep
with Mother.

293
00:18:01,190 --> 00:18:04,250
Of course,
a married couple should share a bed.

294
00:18:04,490 --> 00:18:08,890
You'll say anything
in front of the grandchildren.

295
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:11,430
Grandma,
we're all grown up, you know.

296
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:15,200
Grandma, your face is turning red.

297
00:18:16,170 --> 00:18:17,200
This kid...

298
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:20,570
Why are you kids acting like this?
Just eat your dinner.

299
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:23,570
- Yes, let's eat. Woo Jae, you...
- Let's eat. Eat up.

300
00:18:24,710 --> 00:18:27,740
Mom, your ears are really red.
Look, they're so red.

301
00:18:27,810 --> 00:18:30,150
- Her ears are red.
- They're so red.

302
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:32,180
(Taehan)

303
00:18:32,220 --> 00:18:34,690
It's been a while
since we all had a meeting together.

304
00:18:34,890 --> 00:18:38,090
I've missed this. The unique energy
of the Design Office.

305
00:18:39,190 --> 00:18:41,560
But what are you doing here?

306
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:46,230
I'm always here, so I guess
I've just gotten used to it...

307
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:47,970
Is there anything for me to do?

308
00:18:48,770 --> 00:18:51,370
Vice President?
Please have some dignity.

309
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:54,270
You're one to talk.

310
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:56,770
I can't even go outside.

311
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:59,080
I'm afraid Director Baek
will beat me up.

312
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:01,850
Okay, now that
Pelliv is successfully...

313
00:19:01,910 --> 00:19:03,710
established in the online market,

314
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:06,720
we now need to expand
our customer contact points offline.

315
00:19:07,050 --> 00:19:10,390
How about we open a pop-up store?
If the response is good,

316
00:19:10,450 --> 00:19:11,820
we can look into opening
an official store.

317
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:16,490
Good. FG should focus on
brand reorganization.

318
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:18,300
Please share your ideas
and suggestions...

319
00:19:18,360 --> 00:19:20,100
on how we can win back
our customers' trust.

320
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:25,200
How about we invite
our VIP customers for a golf event?

321
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:27,600
I agree.

322
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:30,310
It's a charity event,
so it'll help improve our image,

323
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:32,910
and it's a perfect way to show
that the brand is still strong.

324
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:35,050
Okay. Since this is
the first official event...

325
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:37,050
since Taehan Fashion's founding,

326
00:19:37,210 --> 00:19:39,450
I need everyone to put special care
into the preparations.

327
00:19:43,090 --> 00:19:45,660
Ms. Gong.
Can I see you for a minute?

328
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:05,940
So, have you thought about
what we discussed yesterday?

329
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:10,610
What? Yes, I did think about it,
but not really...

330
00:20:10,810 --> 00:20:12,950
Then can I go first?

331
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,590
Go first with what?

332
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:25,360
(Yang Hyun Bin's Strategy
For Gong Ju Ah)

333
00:20:26,860 --> 00:20:28,970
To convey my feelings
more accurately,

334
00:20:29,030 --> 00:20:30,430
I prepared a presentation.

335
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:34,810
- You didn't have to do all this.
- I'll get to the conclusion.

336
00:20:35,070 --> 00:20:36,410
My ultimate goal is...

337
00:20:37,940 --> 00:20:39,880
(Yang Hyun Bin's Strategy
To Marry Gong Ju Ah)

338
00:20:42,310 --> 00:20:43,350
to marry you.

339
00:20:44,110 --> 00:20:46,180
To achieve that goal,
I will take responsibility...

340
00:20:46,220 --> 00:20:47,780
for removing all obstacles
in advance.

341
00:20:49,350 --> 00:20:51,960
There are two main obstacles. First.

342
00:20:53,660 --> 00:20:54,660
My mother.

343
00:20:55,060 --> 00:20:57,030
As a stressor for Dr. Han Seong Mi,

344
00:20:57,090 --> 00:20:58,200
who is currently ill,

345
00:20:58,260 --> 00:20:59,460
the risk of conflict
with her mother-in-law...

346
00:20:59,530 --> 00:21:01,800
and living with in-laws' hardships
have been identified as concerns.

347
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,970
I will counter my mother
with a strategy...

348
00:21:04,030 --> 00:21:07,200
- of blocking and controlling.
- Blocking and controlling?

349
00:21:07,770 --> 00:21:09,570
Mother, from now on,
you must maintain...

350
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:11,410
physical distance from
my wife and me.

351
00:21:11,810 --> 00:21:14,240
What? Physical distancing?

352
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:15,880
What's that?

353
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:18,080
The location of our newlywed home
will not be disclosed,

354
00:21:18,380 --> 00:21:21,080
and during family events
such as holidays and birthdays,

355
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:23,850
we will schedule overseas trips
and other external events...

356
00:21:23,990 --> 00:21:26,190
to completely block
any possible contact...

357
00:21:26,260 --> 00:21:27,790
between Mother and Ju Ah.

358
00:21:33,260 --> 00:21:36,530
Mother, that aggressive stare
is also strictly forbidden...

359
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:39,070
- from now on.
- Hey, Yang Hyun Bin!

360
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,200
Second.

361
00:21:41,840 --> 00:21:44,310
My grandfather, who is against us
becoming double in-laws.

362
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:47,940
Since he values
traditional family views...

363
00:21:48,010 --> 00:21:49,010
and customs,

364
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:51,310
I will persuade him with sound logic
and evidence.

365
00:21:53,820 --> 00:21:55,890
What? What did you just say?

366
00:21:56,220 --> 00:21:59,820
Considering double in-laws taboo
is just an outdated way of thinking.

367
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:01,890
Furthermore, it is not grounds
for prohibiting marriage...

368
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:02,960
under civil law,

369
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:05,260
so there are no legal problems
at all.

370
00:22:05,530 --> 00:22:06,860
But if the two families...

371
00:22:06,930 --> 00:22:08,530
If the two families are intertwined,

372
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:11,270
you're worried that a small conflict
could escalate, aren't you?

373
00:22:11,970 --> 00:22:13,600
That's not true. On the contrary,

374
00:22:13,670 --> 00:22:15,940
it will maximize the bond
between our families,

375
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:19,110
creating the optimal structure
for an even stronger relationship.

376
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:30,250
So what happens after you solve
both of those issues?

377
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:31,820
Then, I'll go to your house.

378
00:22:32,090 --> 00:22:33,620
- My house?
- Yes.

379
00:22:35,590 --> 00:22:37,860
A strategy I'm benchmarking
from Dae Han.

380
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:44,230
I'm here, Father, Mother.

381
00:22:45,740 --> 00:22:47,540
What is all this?

382
00:22:51,580 --> 00:22:55,210
I, Yang Hyun Bin, want to spend
the rest of my life with Gong Ju Ah.

383
00:22:55,550 --> 00:22:57,310
Please give us your permission
to marry.

384
00:23:00,220 --> 00:23:01,220
What's going on?

385
00:23:03,420 --> 00:23:06,860
Please give me your permission,
Father, Mother!

386
00:23:19,340 --> 00:23:22,540
- Hey, but...
- Why? You don't think I can do it?

387
00:23:23,510 --> 00:23:25,110
You saw me protect
the Fashion Division.

388
00:23:25,180 --> 00:23:26,680
When I say I'll do something,
I do it.

389
00:23:26,780 --> 00:23:29,110
Okay, I get it. But...

390
00:23:29,410 --> 00:23:30,580
About us.

391
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:33,520
What if we just date?

392
00:23:34,650 --> 00:23:36,850
So you mean we date
and then get married?

393
00:23:37,090 --> 00:23:40,490
No, does marriage have to be
the end goal?

394
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:42,490
What do you mean?

395
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:48,470
To be honest, I'm not sure if I want
to get married.

396
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:51,570
If I get married,
my life will change,

397
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:53,870
and I'll have more responsibilities.

398
00:23:54,470 --> 00:23:56,170
It's not just about being a wife.

399
00:23:56,610 --> 00:24:01,010
- I'd have to become a mother soon.
- Of course.

400
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:05,450
Hyun Bin, I really like you.

401
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:08,590
You're so important to me.

402
00:24:09,650 --> 00:24:11,990
But you don't want to get married?

403
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:16,560
It's not about forcing the marriage
against our families' wishes.

404
00:24:16,830 --> 00:24:19,200
How can we live like this
our whole lives? They're our family.

405
00:24:19,830 --> 00:24:20,830
So?

406
00:24:22,670 --> 00:24:26,100
Well, instead of marriage...

407
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:28,340
What about moving in together?

408
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:35,580
I think of living together
as a trial run for marriage.

409
00:24:35,710 --> 00:24:39,780
If we live together,
I'll still want to get married.

410
00:24:39,980 --> 00:24:43,190
No, why does marriage have to be
our future?

411
00:24:43,290 --> 00:24:45,920
Can't we just have our relationship
on our own terms?

412
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:47,620
What are you really trying to say?

413
00:24:49,060 --> 00:24:52,060
I'm saying it's too soon for me.

414
00:24:52,460 --> 00:24:54,460
There's still so much I want to do,

415
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,930
and I don't want to get married
and settle down.

416
00:24:58,540 --> 00:25:02,670
So the reason we broke up wasn't
because our families are enemies.

417
00:25:03,410 --> 00:25:04,440
You...

418
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:08,680
You just weren't ready
to share a future with me.

419
00:25:13,650 --> 00:25:14,990
What do you want to do then?

420
00:25:18,290 --> 00:25:21,360
I don't want to be strangers.

421
00:25:21,990 --> 00:25:24,460
Okay, so what do you want to do?

422
00:25:25,060 --> 00:25:28,630
Can we just be friends?

423
00:25:35,540 --> 00:25:37,710
Fine. Okay. Let's be friends.

424
00:25:37,770 --> 00:25:41,680
But I can't be your friend
while I'm still in love with you.

425
00:25:42,180 --> 00:25:44,180
I'll try to be a real friend to you.

426
00:25:45,180 --> 00:25:47,650
Okay. Thank you.

427
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,590
Hey, you...

428
00:25:54,420 --> 00:25:56,590
You never planned on marrying
Director Yang?

429
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:59,730
Wait, so then the thing about
Dr. Han being sick...

430
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:01,460
and you not liking
Director Yang's mother,

431
00:26:01,530 --> 00:26:02,570
that was all just an excuse?

432
00:26:03,270 --> 00:26:06,940
- Was it an excuse?
- You weren't head over heels.

433
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:09,670
I like him a lot too.

434
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:12,780
If you really did,
you would've never broken up. Right?

435
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:14,910
You would've been determined
to overcome anything...

436
00:26:14,980 --> 00:26:16,110
and found a way through it.

437
00:26:16,550 --> 00:26:20,180
No, I mean, seriously.

438
00:26:20,350 --> 00:26:24,520
Hey, have you ever told
Director Yang that you love him?

439
00:26:30,490 --> 00:26:32,900
- So I haven't.
- Come on.

440
00:26:33,330 --> 00:26:37,930
I mean, I just wanted to date more,
try living together,

441
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,200
and take things slowly...

442
00:26:39,270 --> 00:26:41,910
Take things slowly? Give me a break.

443
00:26:41,970 --> 00:26:44,370
Director Yang is putting
his entire life on the line for you.

444
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:46,740
Don't lead him on
if you have no intention...

445
00:26:46,810 --> 00:26:47,810
of marrying him.

446
00:26:48,450 --> 00:26:51,410
- Lead him on?
- Yes, lead him on. Get it?

447
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:53,350
Think about it.
Honestly, how devoted...

448
00:26:53,450 --> 00:26:54,650
has Director Yang been to you?

449
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:56,450
He confessed his feelings
so many times.

450
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:58,220
But you just kept playing
with his heart...

451
00:26:58,290 --> 00:26:59,990
and rejected him over and over.

452
00:27:01,990 --> 00:27:03,030
I guess that's true.

453
00:27:04,030 --> 00:27:05,830
I guess we were on different pages.

454
00:27:06,330 --> 00:27:09,370
Well, to be honest...

455
00:27:09,970 --> 00:27:12,170
you were the only one
putting in the effort.

456
00:27:13,670 --> 00:27:14,670
I see.

457
00:27:14,970 --> 00:27:16,310
But...

458
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:19,110
they do say it's better
for the marriage...

459
00:27:19,180 --> 00:27:20,980
when the man is more in love.

460
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:23,610
So what? I should beg her some more?

461
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:27,720
No, why would you beg her?
Just a little...

462
00:27:27,780 --> 00:27:30,050
I'm just saying you should
push her a little more.

463
00:27:30,750 --> 00:27:34,490
If she loved me so much that
she couldn't break up with me,

464
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:36,760
and was willing
to overcome anything,

465
00:27:36,830 --> 00:27:40,860
then I'd try harder too.
But she's so unsure and hesitant.

466
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:42,970
How can I force her into it?

467
00:27:43,300 --> 00:27:44,300
That's true...

468
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:48,040
Marriage isn't something
you can make happen on your own.

469
00:27:48,570 --> 00:27:50,210
If we both wanted it,

470
00:27:50,710 --> 00:27:53,840
we would've gotten married
before my aunt did.

471
00:28:01,580 --> 00:28:03,320
Gosh, this herbal medicine
is so bitter.

472
00:28:03,990 --> 00:28:06,990
Should I complain to your dad?

473
00:28:07,660 --> 00:28:10,930
All herbal medicine is bitter.
Here, have a piece of candy.

474
00:28:11,460 --> 00:28:14,460
Gosh. Dolphin should have one, too.

475
00:28:15,070 --> 00:28:16,070
Here you go.

476
00:28:16,630 --> 00:28:17,630
I'll have one.

477
00:28:18,230 --> 00:28:19,570
Here, you finish this.

478
00:28:20,340 --> 00:28:24,440
What is this? Looks like you two
already claimed this spot.

479
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,080
I'm sorry.

480
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:28,280
So you two are
an official couple now,

481
00:28:28,340 --> 00:28:29,350
out in the open.

482
00:28:29,610 --> 00:28:34,280
- Yes, well, he proposed to me.
- My goodness.

483
00:28:34,350 --> 00:28:36,050
Really?

484
00:28:36,750 --> 00:28:38,860
- So the proposal was a success.
- Yes.

485
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:43,890
We're moving on from just dating
to marriage.

486
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:47,660
- Wonderful. Congratulations.
- Thank you.

487
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:51,270
- Why are you drinking medicine?
- This?

488
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:54,600
We're trying for a baby.

489
00:28:55,510 --> 00:28:58,310
A mini Mr. Gong?
Just imagining it is so cute.

490
00:28:58,540 --> 00:29:02,080
I know, right?
It's not easy at our age,

491
00:29:02,250 --> 00:29:03,310
but we're going to try our best.

492
00:29:03,980 --> 00:29:05,520
I hope we hear good news soon.

493
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:07,420
We will.

494
00:29:07,420 --> 00:29:11,450
Should I add promoting childbirth
to my platform? Go, go, go.

495
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:14,290
- Go for it.
- Go for it.

496
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,360
Mr. Gong.

497
00:29:16,990 --> 00:29:20,430
Hey, so did you submit the papers
to leave the party?

498
00:29:20,430 --> 00:29:24,230
Yes. They processed it right away,
as if they had been waiting for it.

499
00:29:25,270 --> 00:29:27,900
To run as an independent,
you need signatures...

500
00:29:27,970 --> 00:29:30,070
from over 100 supporters, you know?

501
00:29:30,470 --> 00:29:33,080
Do you think
I'll even be able to get them?

502
00:29:33,340 --> 00:29:35,350
Hey, come on.

503
00:29:35,550 --> 00:29:38,280
Where'd that confident Bucket
I used to know go?

504
00:29:38,350 --> 00:29:42,720
- What? Getting cold feet?
- Hey, I even lost to you.

505
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:44,420
What chance do I have
against Councilor Hwang?

506
00:29:44,890 --> 00:29:47,220
I'm also worried
I'll run for nothing,

507
00:29:47,290 --> 00:29:49,030
only to fade into obscurity.

508
00:29:49,090 --> 00:29:53,100
This guy. Hey, I'm Gong Jeong Han.

509
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:55,330
Hey, you. Get up. Get up.

510
00:29:55,600 --> 00:29:56,730
Let's go to
the Merchants' Association Hall.

511
00:29:57,030 --> 00:29:58,430
- The Merchants' Association Hall?
- Yes.

512
00:29:58,500 --> 00:29:59,500
Why there?

513
00:29:59,770 --> 00:30:01,840
The merchant executives
are gathering...

514
00:30:01,910 --> 00:30:03,670
to plan your campaign strategy.

515
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:05,840
- Really?
- Yes.

516
00:30:07,510 --> 00:30:10,110
Excuse me. Excuse me, Doctors.

517
00:30:10,450 --> 00:30:11,610
- Yes?
- Hello.

518
00:30:12,180 --> 00:30:13,180
Is it true that...

519
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:15,650
Councilor Hwang is tearing down
our market?

520
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:16,720
Is it true?

521
00:30:18,020 --> 00:30:20,920
Excuse me, where did you hear that?

522
00:30:20,990 --> 00:30:23,230
Yesterday,
Councilor Hwang met separately...

523
00:30:23,290 --> 00:30:24,430
with just the landlords...

524
00:30:24,490 --> 00:30:26,930
and talked about some landmark
or whatever.

525
00:30:28,060 --> 00:30:29,470
That son of a...

526
00:30:30,300 --> 00:30:32,540
He's acting just like I used to.

527
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:37,340
The market isn't going anywhere.
Don't you worry.

528
00:30:37,410 --> 00:30:38,880
- Is that right?
- Yes, yes. Of course.

529
00:30:38,940 --> 00:30:41,440
- Don't worry.
- My goodness.

530
00:30:42,410 --> 00:30:44,280
Dr. Yang, Dr. Gong.

531
00:30:45,580 --> 00:30:46,680
Councilor Hwang,

532
00:30:46,750 --> 00:30:49,090
did you meet with the landlords
separately?

533
00:30:49,190 --> 00:30:52,160
I'm just doing my job.

534
00:30:52,320 --> 00:30:55,390
How could you tell them
you're getting rid of the market?

535
00:30:55,460 --> 00:30:59,730
I'm not getting rid of the market.
I'm creating a landmark.

536
00:31:04,330 --> 00:31:08,470
Dr. Yang,
my campaign is going to run a poll.

537
00:31:09,270 --> 00:31:12,440
- A poll?
- With you an independent candidate.

538
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:16,950
We'll see how you do.

539
00:31:17,850 --> 00:31:20,250
I'm very much looking forward
to the results.

540
00:31:34,300 --> 00:31:36,430
I checked with
the Medical Association.

541
00:31:36,730 --> 00:31:38,530
They said you need to submit
an explanation...

542
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:40,440
for why you didn't get
continuing education...

543
00:31:40,500 --> 00:31:43,440
or report your license for 30 years.

544
00:31:44,110 --> 00:31:47,440
Honey, just in case, you should go
to the university hospital...

545
00:31:47,510 --> 00:31:48,510
and get a checkup.

546
00:31:49,250 --> 00:31:51,080
It would be good to have
a doctor's note...

547
00:31:51,150 --> 00:31:52,950
saying you're fit
to practice medicine.

548
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:58,020
My dear is as smart
and sharp as ever.

549
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:02,660
Honey, let's make this work.

550
00:32:03,090 --> 00:32:06,400
You and Jeong Han,
working side-by-side...

551
00:32:06,460 --> 00:32:07,830
at the hospital...

552
00:32:08,030 --> 00:32:09,370
I really want to see that.

553
00:32:09,770 --> 00:32:11,370
I'll make sure you do.

554
00:32:12,670 --> 00:32:13,970
Is there any more of this?

555
00:32:15,870 --> 00:32:17,810
You're going back to being a doctor?

556
00:32:18,740 --> 00:32:20,580
And I was just thinking
about retiring.

557
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:22,950
What are you talking about,
retiring?

558
00:32:23,350 --> 00:32:25,210
You're still in your prime.

559
00:32:25,280 --> 00:32:28,750
My prime?
I'm old enough to die any day now.

560
00:32:28,820 --> 00:32:32,720
Hey, I was locked up for 30 years
and just got out.

561
00:32:32,790 --> 00:32:34,260
Is that what you should be
saying to me?

562
00:32:35,930 --> 00:32:37,160
People live to be 100.

563
00:32:37,230 --> 00:32:39,460
I'm going to live
for another 30 years.

564
00:32:40,900 --> 00:32:41,900
Sure, whatever.

565
00:32:42,730 --> 00:32:45,640
You can go ahead and live happily
ever after with your wife.

566
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:48,870
I'll just go to the afterlife
and see In Ok.

567
00:32:49,110 --> 00:32:53,080
Hey, why do you keep acting like
you have one foot in the grave?

568
00:32:54,010 --> 00:32:55,110
Gi Cheol.

569
00:32:55,780 --> 00:32:59,250
Everyone has to die.

570
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:02,320
Life is just a brief event...

571
00:33:02,390 --> 00:33:05,290
that happens before you die.

572
00:33:05,590 --> 00:33:08,620
Gosh. What are you talking about?

573
00:33:09,330 --> 00:33:11,560
I'm just saying it's a brief event.

574
00:33:12,730 --> 00:33:13,800
Gosh.

575
00:33:14,230 --> 00:33:15,870
(Sunhwa Real Estate)

576
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:21,870
Don't tell anyone
I'm liquidating my assets.

577
00:33:21,940 --> 00:33:24,240
Yes, sir. Goodbye.

578
00:33:28,210 --> 00:33:31,980
So Hye, I'm at a real estate office
about Pelliv's office.

579
00:33:32,180 --> 00:33:34,620
Mr. Yang. So Hye, hold on.

580
00:33:35,490 --> 00:33:36,550
Hello.

581
00:33:36,990 --> 00:33:38,090
Who...

582
00:33:39,390 --> 00:33:40,390
Sorry?

583
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:43,430
I'm the granddaughter
from the clinic, sir.

584
00:33:48,660 --> 00:33:49,870
Sir, sir.

585
00:33:50,900 --> 00:33:52,740
- My gosh.
- Are you okay?

586
00:33:52,800 --> 00:33:54,240
Someone call 911.

587
00:33:54,970 --> 00:33:56,610
- Are you all right?
- No.

588
00:33:56,670 --> 00:33:57,840
Call 911...

589
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:01,610
Yes, an elderly man collapsed.

590
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:02,850
(Emergency Medical Center)

591
00:34:13,160 --> 00:34:14,860
Is he unconscious?

592
00:34:15,860 --> 00:34:18,460
No, he just fell asleep
a moment ago.

593
00:34:20,330 --> 00:34:21,860
But why the blood transfusion?

594
00:34:22,230 --> 00:34:24,600
Can you step outside for a second?

595
00:34:27,770 --> 00:34:29,340
(Family Waiting Room)

596
00:34:29,470 --> 00:34:33,780
- Acute Myeloid Leukemia?
- Yes.

597
00:34:34,340 --> 00:34:37,280
I think he knew.

598
00:34:37,750 --> 00:34:42,320
- What?
- He came in for a bone marrow test.

599
00:34:44,590 --> 00:34:47,160
So what's his condition?
Can he survive...

600
00:34:47,220 --> 00:34:49,560
with just a bone marrow transplant?

601
00:34:49,830 --> 00:34:53,130
The hospital wanted to start
with chemotherapy...

602
00:34:53,330 --> 00:34:56,770
and then consider a transplant
depending on his progress,

603
00:34:58,070 --> 00:35:00,900
but your grandfather refused.

604
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:05,480
- Why?
- At his age, with a transplant,

605
00:35:05,780 --> 00:35:07,810
it might be difficult.

606
00:35:10,410 --> 00:35:11,580
So that's why...

607
00:35:11,850 --> 00:35:14,150
he didn't tell anyone
and kept it to himself...

608
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:16,190
So that's why...

609
00:35:16,820 --> 00:35:19,160
he was in such a hurry
for me to get married.

610
00:35:47,320 --> 00:35:50,050
Thank you. Gi Cheol's granddaughter.

611
00:35:50,490 --> 00:35:54,520
- It's nothing.
- You're not dating Hyun Bin again?

612
00:35:55,590 --> 00:36:00,130
No, of course not.
Don't worry. We're just friends.

613
00:36:01,600 --> 00:36:05,370
I have a favor to ask.
Don't tell Gi Cheol that I'm sick.

614
00:36:06,500 --> 00:36:07,500
Okay.

615
00:36:08,470 --> 00:36:10,070
I'm not getting the transplant.

616
00:36:10,740 --> 00:36:15,240
- Grandfather.
- I might die even if I get it.

617
00:36:15,510 --> 00:36:17,480
Don't tell the rest of the family.

618
00:36:17,650 --> 00:36:20,650
Then at least get chemotherapy.

619
00:36:22,820 --> 00:36:25,050
Then what are you going to do?

620
00:36:25,050 --> 00:36:27,160
What if you collapse
on a street again?

621
00:36:32,130 --> 00:36:34,430
Make a decision.
Should I tell the family?

622
00:36:34,500 --> 00:36:35,930
Or will you get Chemotherapy?

623
00:36:38,370 --> 00:36:39,370
You...

624
00:36:39,970 --> 00:36:41,440
Hey, Yang Hyun Bin.

625
00:36:42,100 --> 00:36:43,240
Are you serious?

626
00:36:43,540 --> 00:36:44,540
Yes.

627
00:36:44,870 --> 00:36:47,140
I'm signing up
with a matchmaking agency.

628
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:50,110
If you're going to be a devil,
act like one.

629
00:36:50,180 --> 00:36:52,250
- Are you sick...
- Quiet.

630
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:56,090
Just set me up on blind dates,
matchmaking meetings, anything.

631
00:36:56,350 --> 00:36:58,960
I've decided to do
as Grandfather says.

632
00:36:59,360 --> 00:37:01,290
Wait, Hyun Bin.

633
00:37:03,530 --> 00:37:04,530
Father.

634
00:37:10,770 --> 00:37:14,700
He's finally grown up.
He's finally matured.

635
00:37:18,870 --> 00:37:20,610
I'm worried sick.

636
00:37:21,810 --> 00:37:25,210
What's the big deal?
We're just friends.

637
00:37:28,150 --> 00:37:31,220
Director Yang is putting
his entire life on the line for you.

638
00:37:31,220 --> 00:37:32,620
Don't lead him on
if you have no intention...

639
00:37:32,620 --> 00:37:33,890
of marrying him.

640
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:46,670
Oh my, Hyun Bin.

641
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:49,570
Are you really going on blind dates
with Ju Ah still in the picture?

642
00:37:50,610 --> 00:37:51,610
Forget it.

643
00:37:51,940 --> 00:37:54,110
Labellin is also signing
a partnership deal...

644
00:37:54,180 --> 00:37:55,180
with Taehan Fashion.

645
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:57,580
Never mind that.
The CEO already told me.

646
00:37:57,650 --> 00:37:59,950
Are you really going to marry
someone else?

647
00:38:00,180 --> 00:38:02,750
- What's it to you?
- But even after you broke up,

648
00:38:02,820 --> 00:38:04,890
you were devoted to Ju Ah,
weren't you?

649
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:07,790
You acted like you would never marry
anyone but her.

650
00:38:10,360 --> 00:38:12,560
This is really strange.

651
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:16,670
- What's strange?
- Hyun Bin is.

652
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:20,970
He swore he'd never get married.
What did Father say to him...

653
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:22,410
to make him change his mind
like that?

654
00:38:23,270 --> 00:38:26,040
I guess he had a change of heart.

655
00:38:26,940 --> 00:38:29,750
But the fact that he agreed
to go on blind dates...

656
00:38:30,310 --> 00:38:32,650
must mean he's completely given up
on Jeong Han's daughter, right?

657
00:38:33,020 --> 00:38:35,280
Of course he should, dear.

658
00:38:36,750 --> 00:38:37,850
But something's strange.

659
00:38:39,660 --> 00:38:42,660
You need to be admitted right away
and start chemotherapy.

660
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:46,130
The doctor said...

661
00:38:46,430 --> 00:38:48,100
there are patients older than you,
Grandfather,

662
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:49,870
who have had successful
bone marrow transplants...

663
00:38:49,970 --> 00:38:51,570
and are now living healthy lives.

664
00:38:54,940 --> 00:38:58,210
And I'll sign up with
the matchmaking agency.

665
00:38:58,770 --> 00:39:00,480
I'll even go on the blind dates.

666
00:39:03,110 --> 00:39:06,280
But you can't tell
the rest of the family.

667
00:39:06,850 --> 00:39:08,320
You'll be the only one
visiting me at the hospital.

668
00:39:08,580 --> 00:39:11,250
But you have to be admitted.
What excuse are you going to use?

669
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:13,660
Don't worry. I have a plan.

670
00:39:15,290 --> 00:39:16,760
You're going on a trip?

671
00:39:17,090 --> 00:39:18,090
Yes.

672
00:39:18,590 --> 00:39:20,660
Here and there,
wherever my feet take me.

673
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:22,530
I'm going to wander aimlessly.

674
00:39:23,070 --> 00:39:25,300
With who? A woman?

675
00:39:25,740 --> 00:39:26,740
A man.

676
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:28,840
An old friend, an acupuncturist
who retired this spring.

677
00:39:29,210 --> 00:39:30,210
A friend?

678
00:39:30,910 --> 00:39:32,070
A closer friend than me?

679
00:39:32,410 --> 00:39:33,540
Why, are you jealous?

680
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:35,040
Yes.

681
00:39:35,580 --> 00:39:38,150
Hey, who just up and retires
like this?

682
00:39:38,450 --> 00:39:40,380
It wasn't sudden.

683
00:39:41,450 --> 00:39:44,650
After what happened to In Ok,

684
00:39:45,150 --> 00:39:47,220
I've been thinking
about it constantly.

685
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:50,630
So you want me to be
responsible for your kids?

686
00:39:51,190 --> 00:39:54,360
Yes.

687
00:39:54,900 --> 00:39:59,670
Make sure Dong Ik wins
the city council election.

688
00:39:59,940 --> 00:40:01,870
And take care of things
when Dong Suk gives birth.

689
00:40:02,470 --> 00:40:03,470
All right?

690
00:40:05,940 --> 00:40:07,880
Thank you for coming back,
my friend.

691
00:40:17,450 --> 00:40:19,920
Yes, thank you for coming
all the way to my office for this.

692
00:40:20,560 --> 00:40:23,990
It's quite common.
Everyone's so busy these days.

693
00:40:27,700 --> 00:40:28,700
Here.

694
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:30,700
This is my certificate
of marital status...

695
00:40:30,770 --> 00:40:32,330
and all the documents you asked for.

696
00:40:32,400 --> 00:40:35,700
Thank you.
Okay, then. Shall we start with...

697
00:40:35,770 --> 00:40:37,640
what you're looking for
in a partner?

698
00:40:41,210 --> 00:40:43,310
Someone with a darker complexion,

699
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:46,380
and I prefer a short bob.

700
00:40:46,650 --> 00:40:50,290
- So, the exact opposite of her?
- Yes.

701
00:40:50,290 --> 00:40:51,320
Okay.

702
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:53,360
As long as she's not in my industry.

703
00:40:53,660 --> 00:40:55,090
I can't stand the thought
of working together.

704
00:40:55,890 --> 00:40:57,530
Whether she's religious or not
doesn't matter,

705
00:40:57,830 --> 00:40:59,300
and for personality,
I'd like someone...

706
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:00,360
who is kind and gentle.

707
00:41:00,460 --> 00:41:03,330
I especially want to avoid anyone
who's overly opinionated...

708
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:05,130
and stubborn. That's a deal-breaker.

709
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:06,870
Unbelievable.

710
00:41:07,840 --> 00:41:08,870
All right.

711
00:41:09,270 --> 00:41:12,310
What kind of views on marriage
would you want her to have?

712
00:41:15,140 --> 00:41:16,680
Someone who's willing
to compromise on their goals,

713
00:41:17,010 --> 00:41:20,120
for the sake of the relationship.

714
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:22,850
Someone who doesn't run
away from challenges,

715
00:41:23,620 --> 00:41:26,160
but works to overcome them together.

716
00:41:31,330 --> 00:41:32,700
(Matchmaker, Kang Yu Mi)

717
00:41:33,330 --> 00:41:36,670
Why on earth are you meeting
with a matchmaking agency here?

718
00:41:36,730 --> 00:41:37,770
Didn't you hear?

719
00:41:38,070 --> 00:41:40,700
I'm busy, and she said
she could come to me.

720
00:41:41,600 --> 00:41:44,840
What, are you trying to win me back,

721
00:41:44,910 --> 00:41:46,680
by making me jealous?

722
00:41:47,340 --> 00:41:49,450
Don't you think
you're being a little...

723
00:41:49,510 --> 00:41:52,310
self-centered, my friend?
My grandfather is sick,

724
00:41:52,380 --> 00:41:54,280
so I'm trying to get married
quickly.

725
00:41:55,520 --> 00:41:57,820
You have no consideration
for the people you work with.

726
00:41:57,890 --> 00:42:00,660
Then go work in the Design Office.
Why are you working here?

727
00:42:01,060 --> 00:42:02,890
This is ridiculous.

728
00:42:03,460 --> 00:42:06,700
Fine. I'll go to the Design Office
starting tomorrow.

729
00:42:09,030 --> 00:42:10,300
Get up.

730
00:42:10,500 --> 00:42:14,740
I said I'll go tomorrow.
I have so much stuff right now.

731
00:42:15,040 --> 00:42:17,640
No, I mean let's go
to the outstanding store.

732
00:42:17,870 --> 00:42:19,780
We were supposed to get
gift recommendations...

733
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:21,280
for the VIPs coming to the store.

734
00:42:33,490 --> 00:42:35,160
What kind of items
can I recommend for you?

735
00:42:35,620 --> 00:42:38,690
These are for a VIP event,

736
00:42:38,930 --> 00:42:41,530
so please recommend items
that have been popular recently.

737
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:44,970
This line here has products
that customers...

738
00:42:45,030 --> 00:42:46,500
have been looking for lately.

739
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:51,070
I thought they'd prefer
a more classic style,

740
00:42:51,210 --> 00:42:53,140
but there are more flashy items
than I expected.

741
00:42:53,210 --> 00:42:56,050
These days,
rather than subdued items,

742
00:42:56,110 --> 00:42:57,310
people are definitely looking for...

743
00:42:57,380 --> 00:42:58,910
colors or materials
that make a statement.

744
00:42:59,720 --> 00:43:02,080
We also need some accessories
to go with them.

745
00:43:02,150 --> 00:43:03,420
What's been selling well?

746
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:05,590
Practical items like these
are very popular.

747
00:43:06,020 --> 00:43:07,020
Yes.

748
00:43:10,060 --> 00:43:11,360
In that case,

749
00:43:12,060 --> 00:43:14,600
let's make the accessories
a standard set for everyone,

750
00:43:14,660 --> 00:43:16,830
and for the clothes, we can research
our clients' tastes,

751
00:43:16,900 --> 00:43:18,300
and prepare customized options.
What do you think?

752
00:43:18,870 --> 00:43:20,640
Excellent. Let's proceed with that.

753
00:43:22,240 --> 00:43:23,340
Oh my.

754
00:43:25,140 --> 00:43:29,140
Since the event gift package is set,

755
00:43:29,910 --> 00:43:31,610
let's finalize
the VIP invitation list...

756
00:43:31,680 --> 00:43:32,680
by our next meeting.

757
00:43:33,080 --> 00:43:35,380
Okay, you're going to the office,
right?

758
00:43:35,720 --> 00:43:37,650
No, I'm going straight home.

759
00:43:38,090 --> 00:43:41,720
I have to go to the office.
Ms. Shim wanted to see me.

760
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:43,430
I see.

761
00:43:44,060 --> 00:43:47,960
Then I'll drop you
at the subway station, my friend.

762
00:43:49,400 --> 00:43:51,330
You're so petty, my friend.

763
00:43:56,210 --> 00:43:59,410
Wow, they've already sent
a potential match's profile.

764
00:44:02,850 --> 00:44:07,080
If she was born in 1999,
isn't that too young?

765
00:44:07,280 --> 00:44:08,320
How old is she?

766
00:44:08,620 --> 00:44:10,250
Is that a real question?
Can you not do simple math?

767
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:13,190
Works in research and development
at a global beauty brand.

768
00:44:16,630 --> 00:44:18,030
Studied abroad in Buenos Aires.

769
00:44:18,860 --> 00:44:20,000
Oh my, awesome.

770
00:44:20,400 --> 00:44:22,360
It says her hobby is
going on food tours.

771
00:44:22,900 --> 00:44:24,100
What do you think?

772
00:44:24,800 --> 00:44:26,700
Why are you asking me?

773
00:44:26,940 --> 00:44:31,640
As my friend and my ex,
you can tell me that much, right?

774
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:34,980
(Yoon Seo Ah)

775
00:44:35,580 --> 00:44:36,610
She's nothing special.

776
00:44:37,150 --> 00:44:38,150
Really?

777
00:44:39,950 --> 00:44:41,250
I think she's pretty.

778
00:44:42,680 --> 00:44:44,150
You have terrible taste.

779
00:44:48,620 --> 00:44:51,390
(Groom Choi Se Hyun,
Bride Shin Bo Mi)

780
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:57,000
Wait, you two are getting married
already?

781
00:44:57,100 --> 00:44:59,900
Yes, in a month. You'll come, right?

782
00:45:00,070 --> 00:45:01,870
Wow, so we're finally
getting our first...

783
00:45:01,940 --> 00:45:03,610
in-office married couple
on the team?

784
00:45:04,370 --> 00:45:09,040
But you're both so young
to be getting married.

785
00:45:09,480 --> 00:45:14,180
Our parents were actually
against it, but we insisted.

786
00:45:14,350 --> 00:45:15,480
Why?

787
00:45:16,090 --> 00:45:19,350
Do you have good news?

788
00:45:19,960 --> 00:45:23,090
- No, that's not it.
- Then why?

789
00:45:24,060 --> 00:45:25,060
Why?

790
00:45:25,990 --> 00:45:27,460
Did we need a reason?

791
00:45:29,470 --> 00:45:30,470
Because we're in love.

792
00:45:32,300 --> 00:45:33,640
Because we hate being apart.

793
00:45:36,270 --> 00:45:39,040
That's the spirit.
Right? Hey, you two.

794
00:45:43,210 --> 00:45:45,650
- I'm back.
- Hey.

795
00:45:45,650 --> 00:45:46,720
Look at this.

796
00:45:46,720 --> 00:45:48,120
For doctors who've opened
their own clinics,

797
00:45:48,150 --> 00:45:49,550
there are so many training courses.

798
00:45:49,790 --> 00:45:52,550
You're right. Wow,
Korea University Hospital...

799
00:45:52,620 --> 00:45:54,260
offers a lot of good ones.

800
00:45:54,390 --> 00:45:57,390
Going to a big hospital
might jog my memory.

801
00:45:57,560 --> 00:46:00,000
- Want to go together?
- Sure. Let's go together.

802
00:46:02,800 --> 00:46:06,170
- Gosh, this really hurts inside.
- I'm home.

803
00:46:06,170 --> 00:46:07,800
- Hey.
- Hey.

804
00:46:07,800 --> 00:46:09,470
How does it feel?

805
00:46:09,870 --> 00:46:11,870
The breeze from the fan
feels much better.

806
00:46:13,580 --> 00:46:14,810
Before you go to sleep,

807
00:46:14,880 --> 00:46:17,750
I'll put a cold compress on it
and apply your ointment.

808
00:46:18,210 --> 00:46:20,380
Thank you. You're the best.

809
00:46:22,320 --> 00:46:25,750
- What? You have something to say?
- No, it's nothing.

810
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:30,790
- The rehab program looks good.
- This would be good to take too.

811
00:46:30,860 --> 00:46:31,860
What about this one?

812
00:46:36,970 --> 00:46:39,430
You all seem so happy.

813
00:46:39,900 --> 00:46:41,040
You startled me.

814
00:46:41,540 --> 00:46:43,740
Of course I'm happy.

815
00:46:44,010 --> 00:46:48,080
Right. Gong Ju Ah. Officer Jeong
and Nurse Oh will marry.

816
00:46:48,910 --> 00:46:51,180
Really?

817
00:46:52,750 --> 00:46:54,080
That was surprising, wasn't it?

818
00:46:59,290 --> 00:47:02,490
Why aren't you sleeping?
Why'd you call?

819
00:47:03,260 --> 00:47:05,790
I saw. Did you tell Dad everything?

820
00:47:05,790 --> 00:47:09,630
Yes, I'm not going to hide
anything from your dad.

821
00:47:09,630 --> 00:47:10,970
I was thinking
I should tell him everything.

822
00:47:11,270 --> 00:47:12,270
Why all of a sudden?

823
00:47:12,970 --> 00:47:15,600
It's not all of a sudden.
I just felt like it was time.

824
00:47:17,140 --> 00:47:19,070
So, why did you want to see me?

825
00:47:21,310 --> 00:47:23,380
- For some counseling.
- Counseling?

826
00:47:23,750 --> 00:47:24,750
Sounds good.

827
00:47:25,150 --> 00:47:28,480
- What is it?
- Counselor mode, not mom mode.

828
00:47:29,920 --> 00:47:32,390
Okay. Go on.

829
00:47:33,360 --> 00:47:35,660
Dr. Han,

830
00:47:36,630 --> 00:47:38,360
why do you think
I broke up with Hyun Bin?

831
00:47:39,460 --> 00:47:41,260
Why all of a sudden?
Did something happen?

832
00:47:41,730 --> 00:47:44,900
- Counselor mode.
- Right, right.

833
00:47:46,940 --> 00:47:47,940
I just...

834
00:47:48,200 --> 00:47:50,510
I want to figure out
what my problem is.

835
00:47:51,170 --> 00:47:52,810
Everyone's rushing to get married,

836
00:47:52,870 --> 00:47:54,780
and all the couples
are so lovey-dovey,

837
00:47:55,080 --> 00:47:56,310
and it makes me wonder
what will happen to me.

838
00:47:56,980 --> 00:48:00,220
I want to learn from my past
so I can move forward.

839
00:48:00,720 --> 00:48:02,580
Why you broke up with
Director Yang...

840
00:48:02,850 --> 00:48:03,990
You ask
because you really don't know?

841
00:48:05,290 --> 00:48:07,320
Maybe because
there were too many obstacles?

842
00:48:07,590 --> 00:48:11,860
Gong Ju Ah, who always gets her way
no matter what?

843
00:48:12,460 --> 00:48:15,100
Weren't they huge obstacles?
Our families are enemies,

844
00:48:15,200 --> 00:48:17,200
and you and Hyun Bin's mother
don't get along.

845
00:48:17,970 --> 00:48:18,970
Plus, you were sick,

846
00:48:19,030 --> 00:48:20,840
so it was hard for me
to bring it up.

847
00:48:21,440 --> 00:48:23,910
What did your uncle and aunt do
in the same situation?

848
00:48:25,440 --> 00:48:27,910
They never gave up.

849
00:48:28,340 --> 00:48:31,810
Hey, honestly,
Director Yang gave it his all.

850
00:48:32,150 --> 00:48:34,180
He was so good to me
and your grandmother.

851
00:48:34,650 --> 00:48:37,850
But what did you do?
Wait, you did do something.

852
00:48:38,420 --> 00:48:39,420
You gave up.

853
00:48:41,260 --> 00:48:44,360
Are you saying
I wasn't committed enough?

854
00:48:45,260 --> 00:48:46,660
That's for you to know.

855
00:48:48,460 --> 00:48:51,500
So what does it take to get married?

856
00:48:54,440 --> 00:48:57,540
When you can't imagine living
without that person?

857
00:48:58,970 --> 00:49:03,210
No matter what obstacles you face,
when giving up is never an option.

858
00:49:09,320 --> 00:49:11,290
What bombshell
is he planning to drop...

859
00:49:11,350 --> 00:49:13,020
that made him gather all of us?

860
00:49:14,360 --> 00:49:15,390
Grandfather...

861
00:49:15,760 --> 00:49:18,060
is leaving on a cross-country trip
starting tomorrow.

862
00:49:18,530 --> 00:49:19,660
- What?
- What?

863
00:49:19,730 --> 00:49:21,330
What? A cross-country trip?

864
00:49:23,600 --> 00:49:25,000
I'm sending him on the trip.

865
00:49:25,170 --> 00:49:28,500
Wait. Why a cross-country trip
all of a sudden?

866
00:49:28,740 --> 00:49:30,140
Father, why?

867
00:49:31,340 --> 00:49:33,440
Father, then what about...

868
00:49:34,010 --> 00:49:36,140
the clinic?

869
00:49:36,950 --> 00:49:37,950
I'm going to retire.

870
00:49:38,810 --> 00:49:39,820
You figure it out.

871
00:49:40,520 --> 00:49:43,090
Grandfather, what do you mean
you're retiring?

872
00:49:43,150 --> 00:49:44,620
You're still going strong.

873
00:49:44,820 --> 00:49:48,390
Father, I'm going to be busy
with the election.

874
00:49:49,090 --> 00:49:51,660
Hire someone
or figure it out yourself.

875
00:49:51,990 --> 00:49:54,560
Father, why are you being like this
all of a sudden?

876
00:49:54,560 --> 00:49:56,630
Did we do something
to disappoint you?

877
00:49:56,930 --> 00:49:59,700
He wants to spend the rest of his
life doing what he wants,

878
00:49:59,770 --> 00:50:01,570
so why is everyone
trying to stop him?

879
00:50:01,770 --> 00:50:03,740
I know, but still,
Father needs to be here...

880
00:50:03,810 --> 00:50:06,410
- for important family matters.
- For important matters,

881
00:50:07,080 --> 00:50:08,410
get Hyun Bin's permission.

882
00:50:10,480 --> 00:50:12,710
What is this...

883
00:50:16,080 --> 00:50:18,920
(Taehan)

884
00:50:19,720 --> 00:50:20,720
Come in.

885
00:50:29,060 --> 00:50:31,700
Did your grandfather agree
to be hospitalized?

886
00:50:32,070 --> 00:50:33,840
He already has been.

887
00:50:34,270 --> 00:50:35,770
I'm on my way back
from admitting him.

888
00:50:36,000 --> 00:50:37,670
I see.

889
00:50:38,040 --> 00:50:40,480
Well, then, take this with you
when you leave work.

890
00:50:40,740 --> 00:50:42,810
I packed some things for him
for his hospital stay.

891
00:50:43,310 --> 00:50:45,450
Infection control is critical
for leukemia patients,

892
00:50:45,510 --> 00:50:46,720
so they need a lot of things.

893
00:50:47,020 --> 00:50:49,380
When he starts chemotherapy,
he'll lose his hair,

894
00:50:49,450 --> 00:50:50,490
so I bought him a hat.

895
00:50:52,150 --> 00:50:54,220
I appreciate the thought.

896
00:50:54,960 --> 00:50:56,060
What? Why?

897
00:50:56,630 --> 00:50:59,330
When my mom was in the hospital,
you did the same for her.

898
00:50:59,660 --> 00:51:01,430
That was when we were dating.

899
00:51:01,830 --> 00:51:06,100
Come on,
friends can do this much, right?

900
00:51:06,370 --> 00:51:07,840
If I say you gave them to me,

901
00:51:08,170 --> 00:51:09,870
Grandfather will worry
unnecessarily.

902
00:51:10,770 --> 00:51:13,980
He's already sick,
and I don't want to stress him out.

903
00:51:16,310 --> 00:51:17,310
I mean...

904
00:51:20,880 --> 00:51:21,880
Pacu Nacho.

905
00:51:22,220 --> 00:51:24,550
A rumor's going around the office
that you're going on blind dates.

906
00:51:25,020 --> 00:51:26,820
Why are you suddenly in a rush
to get married?

907
00:51:27,090 --> 00:51:29,790
What, are you trying
to make someone jealous?

908
00:51:30,530 --> 00:51:32,660
My grandfather has leukemia.

909
00:51:34,430 --> 00:51:37,330
I think he wants me to get married
before he passes away.

910
00:51:37,870 --> 00:51:40,270
That's why he was putting pressure
on my mother.

911
00:51:42,970 --> 00:51:47,240
No, but still. You're
going to rush into marriage...

912
00:51:47,310 --> 00:51:49,110
with someone you meet
on a blind date?

913
00:51:49,810 --> 00:51:51,510
And leave Ms. Gong,
who you love so much?

914
00:51:51,750 --> 00:51:55,180
Well, what else am I supposed to do?
She said she's not interested.

915
00:51:56,820 --> 00:51:57,850
Didn't she get jealous
when she heard...

916
00:51:57,920 --> 00:52:00,360
- you were going on blind dates?
- It seemed like she did.

917
00:52:00,890 --> 00:52:02,720
What does she want,
asking to be friends?

918
00:52:03,090 --> 00:52:04,890
What if...

919
00:52:06,090 --> 00:52:07,700
it's not that your feelings
are different,

920
00:52:07,760 --> 00:52:09,360
but that you're moving
at different speeds?

921
00:52:09,500 --> 00:52:11,730
Come on, stop giving me hope.

922
00:52:12,070 --> 00:52:14,500
Some people are slow to warm up.

923
00:52:14,970 --> 00:52:17,470
You're impulsive,
and Ms. Gong is cautious.

924
00:52:17,910 --> 00:52:19,940
You've been chasing her
with a one-sided crush...

925
00:52:20,010 --> 00:52:21,010
since you were young,

926
00:52:21,080 --> 00:52:22,280
but that's not the case
for Ms. Gong.

927
00:52:23,580 --> 00:52:27,020
- So what? Telling me to wait?
- Forget waiting.

928
00:52:27,550 --> 00:52:30,420
You need to speed things up.
With a booster.

929
00:52:31,250 --> 00:52:32,490
A booster?

930
00:52:37,530 --> 00:52:42,330
Hey, my sister and Director Yang
are getting married.

931
00:52:43,060 --> 00:52:44,330
Are you okay?

932
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:47,800
What?

933
00:52:47,870 --> 00:52:50,070
Hey, you said you weren't going to
marry Director Yang anyway, right?

934
00:52:50,770 --> 00:52:52,910
Hey, isn't this our chance
to lock Pacu Nacho...

935
00:52:52,970 --> 00:52:55,110
in Taehan forever?

936
00:52:55,210 --> 00:53:00,120
- This is great.
- Marriage isn't a business deal.

937
00:53:00,820 --> 00:53:02,680
Well, it's similar. Marriage is...

938
00:53:02,750 --> 00:53:05,090
ultimately about
managing life together...

939
00:53:05,150 --> 00:53:08,920
- forming a strategic partnership.
- Snap out of it.

940
00:53:09,220 --> 00:53:12,660
You marry the person you love.
Stop your sister.

941
00:53:12,730 --> 00:53:15,200
Hey, why stop her?
This is a jackpot for my sister.

942
00:53:15,360 --> 00:53:16,570
Didn't you know
my sister had a crush...

943
00:53:16,630 --> 00:53:18,000
on Pacu Nacho
when she was studying abroad?

944
00:53:18,330 --> 00:53:21,300
Besides, Pacu Nacho's family
will love her.

945
00:53:21,500 --> 00:53:24,270
- Darn it.
- Hey, Director Yang is in a hurry,

946
00:53:24,340 --> 00:53:26,580
so rather than having him
go on a blind date...

947
00:53:26,780 --> 00:53:29,580
with a total stranger,
this is a thousand times better.

948
00:53:29,640 --> 00:53:30,650
Don't you think?

949
00:53:31,150 --> 00:53:32,180
This is crazy.

950
00:53:32,480 --> 00:53:36,890
- Nacho, Pacu Nacho.
- Yes, my dear.

951
00:53:38,520 --> 00:53:41,660
- Where should we have our wedding?
- Do whatever you want.

952
00:53:42,890 --> 00:53:43,890
Excuse me.

953
00:53:44,890 --> 00:53:49,730
- Buenos Aires for our honeymoon?
- I'd love that.

954
00:53:49,800 --> 00:53:51,530
I'd love that too.

955
00:53:56,370 --> 00:53:58,170
Are you okay?

956
00:53:58,170 --> 00:54:00,110
Are you jealous?

957
00:54:00,180 --> 00:54:02,780
Hey, you're not in a position
to act like this.

958
00:54:02,780 --> 00:54:03,810
Hey, Ju Ah.

959
00:54:06,780 --> 00:54:10,790
(Hanguk University Hospital)

960
00:54:10,850 --> 00:54:14,860
Wow. It's really changed
since I was a resident here.

961
00:54:15,190 --> 00:54:16,260
You remember?

962
00:54:16,560 --> 00:54:19,060
I used to bring you lunch here
all the time back then.

963
00:54:20,160 --> 00:54:22,030
Since Dr. Yang is going on a trip,

964
00:54:22,100 --> 00:54:24,300
I think I'll hang out here
and reminisce.

965
00:54:24,930 --> 00:54:27,200
You're sad that Dr. Yang
is going on a trip, aren't you?

966
00:54:27,570 --> 00:54:28,740
Of course, I am.

967
00:54:30,740 --> 00:54:32,470
Hold on. Which way do we go?

968
00:54:38,380 --> 00:54:39,380
My goodness.

969
00:54:50,960 --> 00:54:51,960
Goodness.

970
00:54:53,830 --> 00:54:54,830
What?

971
00:54:55,100 --> 00:54:58,970
Wait, hey.
Your Father is suddenly retiring?

972
00:54:58,970 --> 00:55:00,040
Apparently.

973
00:55:00,340 --> 00:55:02,640
He just up and left
for a trip this morning.

974
00:55:02,900 --> 00:55:04,210
Jeong Han.

975
00:55:05,540 --> 00:55:07,640
Dong Ik, you're here too?

976
00:55:07,940 --> 00:55:10,210
Yes. Why? What is it?

977
00:55:10,410 --> 00:55:11,850
Well, it is...

978
00:55:12,410 --> 00:55:15,280
Is it about me?

979
00:55:16,480 --> 00:55:18,090
Well...

980
00:55:19,090 --> 00:55:22,720
Councilor Hwang's campaign ran
a poll, and the results are out.

981
00:55:22,860 --> 00:55:26,190
Is that so?
How much did our Dong Ik get?

982
00:55:28,330 --> 00:55:32,330
Why? What was the percentage?
Tell me. It's fine.

983
00:55:32,400 --> 00:55:33,400
I'm not getting my hopes up.

984
00:55:33,670 --> 00:55:34,670
Yes.

985
00:55:37,070 --> 00:55:41,680
No way. Was it 30?
It was not 30, was it?

986
00:55:42,580 --> 00:55:46,150
Then in that case, three percent?

987
00:55:46,780 --> 00:55:48,380
Just three percent.

988
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:51,890
But it's too early
to be disappointed.

989
00:55:52,150 --> 00:55:55,190
There's a zero in front of it,
so it's zero point three percent.

990
00:55:55,520 --> 00:55:56,830
What?

991
00:55:58,330 --> 00:55:59,390
Jeong Han.

992
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:02,800
I'm going home.
I don't think I'll run.

993
00:56:03,000 --> 00:56:06,670
Hey, what are you doing?
We haven't even started yet.

994
00:56:06,740 --> 00:56:09,300
He's right. Don't be discouraged.

995
00:56:09,370 --> 00:56:11,670
- We're here for you. We'll help.
- Of course.

996
00:56:11,740 --> 00:56:12,740
Right.

997
00:56:13,410 --> 00:56:14,510
Zero point three.

998
00:56:15,240 --> 00:56:16,580
I wish that was the interest rate
on a loan.

999
00:56:19,150 --> 00:56:20,320
Zero point three percent?

1000
00:56:20,380 --> 00:56:22,320
(3H Acupressure Bed)

1001
00:56:24,620 --> 00:56:28,190
Honey, don't be so disappointed.
If we campaign hard,

1002
00:56:28,260 --> 00:56:30,530
we can definitely turn
the polls around.

1003
00:56:31,230 --> 00:56:34,100
Okay, talk to you later. All right.

1004
00:56:36,200 --> 00:56:40,440
I'm sorry, something came up.
About what you mentioned,

1005
00:56:40,740 --> 00:56:43,840
- know-how and practical materials.
- Okay.

1006
00:56:45,940 --> 00:56:49,410
My goodness,
you've organized this so well.

1007
00:56:50,510 --> 00:56:52,180
As the owner
of an outstanding store,

1008
00:56:52,250 --> 00:56:53,310
it's the least I can do.

1009
00:56:53,410 --> 00:56:55,180
(Certified Medical Device Bed)

1010
00:56:55,720 --> 00:56:57,590
By the way,
we're gathering people...

1011
00:56:57,650 --> 00:56:59,790
who are interested in
running a center,

1012
00:56:59,850 --> 00:57:01,320
and we're planning to hold
a business briefing.

1013
00:57:01,420 --> 00:57:05,430
How would you feel about leading it?

1014
00:57:05,830 --> 00:57:06,830
Me?

1015
00:57:07,330 --> 00:57:11,530
I don't have any experience.
Do you think I can do a good job?

1016
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:15,770
Of course.
We'll be there to support you,

1017
00:57:15,940 --> 00:57:16,970
so don't worry.

1018
00:57:19,470 --> 00:57:22,040
Well then, since you're putting
your trust in me,

1019
00:57:22,640 --> 00:57:24,210
I'll make sure
to prepare thoroughly.

1020
00:57:28,820 --> 00:57:30,790
Oh my, here you go.

1021
00:57:32,350 --> 00:57:33,720
Thanks, Dong Suk.

1022
00:57:43,800 --> 00:57:45,830
You haven't gone to work
because of me?

1023
00:57:46,400 --> 00:57:48,670
It's fine.
Woo Jae is watching the store.

1024
00:57:49,870 --> 00:57:52,670
I'm really making you
take care of me.

1025
00:57:53,040 --> 00:57:55,840
Don't say that. It's upsetting.

1026
00:57:58,280 --> 00:57:59,810
Who could that be?

1027
00:58:04,620 --> 00:58:07,160
- Who is it?
- It's me.

1028
00:58:07,690 --> 00:58:08,860
It's Cha Se Ri.

1029
00:58:09,660 --> 00:58:13,190
What brings you here so early
without calling?

1030
00:58:13,390 --> 00:58:15,900
- Just open the door.
- Well...

1031
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:17,770
What should I do?

1032
00:58:18,970 --> 00:58:23,300
Let her in.
I'm a mess. I'll go inside and rest.

1033
00:58:25,070 --> 00:58:26,070
Okay.

1034
00:58:33,250 --> 00:58:36,250
Father is suddenly retiring
to travel?

1035
00:58:36,720 --> 00:58:37,720
Yes.

1036
00:58:38,090 --> 00:58:41,990
It seems he's had a change of heart
after Mother passed away.

1037
00:58:42,190 --> 00:58:43,320
I was hoping he could get
some counseling...

1038
00:58:43,390 --> 00:58:45,660
if Dr. Han was here.
Is she in her room?

1039
00:58:46,230 --> 00:58:48,560
She's not in her room. She went out.

1040
00:58:50,100 --> 00:58:51,970
Did she go far?
Should I try calling her?

1041
00:58:52,130 --> 00:58:55,640
It's fine.
I'll tell her when she gets back.

1042
00:58:56,070 --> 00:58:59,010
Then don't forget
to pass on the message.

1043
00:58:59,410 --> 00:59:00,580
Yes, I will.

1044
00:59:01,410 --> 00:59:03,880
But why are you here at this hour?
What about your store?

1045
00:59:05,010 --> 00:59:06,980
I've been so busy going
to the main office...

1046
00:59:07,050 --> 00:59:08,820
that I left the store
to a part-timer.

1047
00:59:09,250 --> 00:59:13,190
Hey, my store was chosen
as an outstanding store this time.

1048
00:59:13,490 --> 00:59:14,490
And can you believe it?

1049
00:59:14,560 --> 00:59:16,590
They even asked me to lead
the business briefing.

1050
00:59:16,860 --> 00:59:19,260
Wow, you're so cool.

1051
00:59:19,690 --> 00:59:21,030
Right? I'm pretty amazing, aren't I?

1052
00:59:21,800 --> 00:59:23,560
My husband is thrilled about it too.

1053
00:59:23,970 --> 00:59:26,370
I mean, it's not like
Dr. Han Seong Mi is the only one...

1054
00:59:26,430 --> 00:59:27,440
who can be successful.

1055
00:59:39,210 --> 00:59:41,150
Who says I'm successful?

1056
00:59:42,120 --> 00:59:43,690
Han Seong Mi is finished.

1057
00:59:52,030 --> 00:59:54,230
I've been calling you.
Have you been busy?

1058
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:59,970
I got some tickets to a play.
Want to go with me, Eun Bin?

1059
01:00:00,900 --> 01:00:01,900
Eun Bin?

1060
01:00:03,770 --> 01:00:06,470
Well, it's just...

1061
01:00:10,380 --> 01:00:12,410
So, should we go
to my place tonight?

1062
01:00:12,580 --> 01:00:14,680
Should we? It's been a while.
Ready for a match?

1063
01:00:14,750 --> 01:00:16,820
Yes, why not? Let's go all out.

1064
01:00:17,250 --> 01:00:18,490
I'm ready for whatever you've got.

1065
01:00:20,920 --> 01:00:23,930
- I'm feeling good today.
- Me too.

1066
01:00:33,170 --> 01:00:35,200
Wow, this looks so delicious.

1067
01:00:35,270 --> 01:00:36,770
- You haven't changed a bit.
- Let's get this too. Now...

1068
01:00:36,840 --> 01:00:38,770
- You still love your snacks.
- This looks delicious too.

1069
01:00:38,840 --> 01:00:39,840
Honestly.

1070
01:00:40,510 --> 01:00:44,350
- Wait. I have something in my eye.
- Let me see.

1071
01:00:47,280 --> 01:00:48,280
What's going on?

1072
01:00:49,180 --> 01:00:50,180
Did I get it?

1073
01:00:50,950 --> 01:00:53,590
How is it? Yes. It's out.

1074
01:00:59,030 --> 01:01:00,800
- Honestly.
- Then leave it.

1075
01:01:00,860 --> 01:01:02,830
Pacu Nacho, you're hilarious.

1076
01:01:03,260 --> 01:01:04,630
Why are you like this?

1077
01:01:08,370 --> 01:01:09,540
What should I do?

1078
01:01:10,440 --> 01:01:12,510
- I said it's out.
- Just let me see.

1079
01:01:13,340 --> 01:01:14,810
I'm so hungry right now.

1080
01:01:16,040 --> 01:01:17,950
Pacu Nacho, I'm exhausted.

1081
01:01:21,150 --> 01:01:22,250
Why am I...

1082
01:01:23,150 --> 01:01:24,450
Why am I being like this?

1083
01:01:25,390 --> 01:01:26,920
You're crazy, Gong Ju Ah.

1084
01:01:29,360 --> 01:01:30,430
No...

1085
01:01:35,760 --> 01:01:36,860
You are so dead.

1086
01:01:37,400 --> 01:01:40,330
- Are your skills still sharp?
- I'm on fire.

1087
01:01:40,640 --> 01:01:42,170
Same here. You'd better watch out.

1088
01:01:42,700 --> 01:01:44,440
- We'll see about that.
- Yes.

1089
01:01:46,740 --> 01:01:49,880
- I'm suddenly getting nervous.
- I knew you would be.

1090
01:01:49,940 --> 01:01:51,350
Gosh, my hands are sweating.

1091
01:01:53,150 --> 01:01:54,820
- Come in.
- Okay.

1092
01:02:02,660 --> 01:02:04,060
How long has it been?

1093
01:02:04,790 --> 01:02:07,530
I'm so excited and nervous.

1094
01:02:11,100 --> 01:02:12,270
My love.

1095
01:02:14,100 --> 01:02:17,640
- I love you.
- Ready for a game? Been a while.

1096
01:02:18,970 --> 01:02:19,970
I'd love to.

1097
01:02:27,080 --> 01:02:30,450
No. Open the door. No.

1098
01:02:31,990 --> 01:02:36,220
No, wait a minute. No, please stop.

1099
01:02:37,630 --> 01:02:38,660
No.

1100
01:02:40,090 --> 01:02:41,100
Ms. Gong.

1101
01:02:45,100 --> 01:02:46,200
What brings you here?

1102
01:02:47,470 --> 01:02:49,970
I was just...

1103
01:02:50,470 --> 01:02:52,440
We were just playing a game
from the old days.

1104
01:02:52,510 --> 01:02:54,380
It's one we used to play
a lot in Argentina.

1105
01:02:54,440 --> 01:02:55,440
Do you want to join us?

1106
01:02:56,710 --> 01:03:01,150
I'm sorry.
I just thought that you two were...

1107
01:03:02,420 --> 01:03:03,890
Looks like our little push worked.

1108
01:03:04,620 --> 01:03:07,220
Well then, I guess I should...

1109
01:03:07,790 --> 01:03:09,190
give you two some space.

1110
01:03:09,920 --> 01:03:11,690
- I'll get going then.
- Okay.

1111
01:03:21,040 --> 01:03:22,370
Why are you here?

1112
01:03:23,300 --> 01:03:25,570
- I don't like it.
- What don't you like?

1113
01:03:26,640 --> 01:03:28,710
I don't like you
being with another woman.

1114
01:03:29,040 --> 01:03:30,550
You said you wanted
to be just friends.

1115
01:03:30,610 --> 01:03:33,010
I can't.
I can't just be friends with you.

1116
01:03:33,280 --> 01:03:37,080
- So what now? You asked for this.
- Marry me.

1117
01:03:37,850 --> 01:03:40,390
- Forget it.
- Why? You wanted to get married.

1118
01:03:40,450 --> 01:03:42,660
You're only doing this
because of my grandfather.

1119
01:03:43,060 --> 01:03:44,090
I love you.

1120
01:03:47,260 --> 01:03:49,360
I love you too, you idiot.

1121
01:03:51,170 --> 01:03:53,940
So don't you dare
see any other women.

1122
01:03:54,070 --> 01:03:57,570
Don't even look at other women.
Only look at me. Got it?

1123
01:04:03,110 --> 01:04:04,110
I'm sorry.

1124
01:04:05,450 --> 01:04:07,180
I'm sorry it took me so long.

1125
01:04:07,850 --> 01:04:08,880
It's okay.

1126
01:04:09,420 --> 01:04:10,620
Thank you for coming.

1127
01:04:11,590 --> 01:04:13,520
I'm sorry for making you wait.

1128
01:04:15,160 --> 01:04:17,090
If you don't want to get married,
you don't have to.

1129
01:04:18,160 --> 01:04:19,930
It's enough for me
that you're here now.

1130
01:04:20,630 --> 01:04:21,630
No.

1131
01:04:21,960 --> 01:04:25,300
I'm not going to run away anymore.
And I'm not giving up on you.

1132
01:04:25,700 --> 01:04:27,370
From now on,
no matter what challenges we face,

1133
01:04:27,970 --> 01:04:29,370
I won't lose you.

1134
01:04:30,170 --> 01:04:32,840
So marry me.
Marry me, Yang Hyun Bin.

1135
01:04:32,910 --> 01:04:33,910
Marry me...

1136
01:04:35,180 --> 01:04:36,440
Okay, I get it.

1137
01:04:37,450 --> 01:04:38,650
Stop talking.

1138
01:05:06,710 --> 01:05:09,640
(Recipe For Love)

1139
01:05:10,750 --> 01:05:12,550
Did you see Ju Ah
come home yesterday?

1140
01:05:12,610 --> 01:05:15,180
You know Ju Ah.
When she likes someone,

1141
01:05:15,250 --> 01:05:17,650
she goes for it and never gives up.

1142
01:05:17,950 --> 01:05:20,190
It seems I've saved you
twice now, Mother.

1143
01:05:21,090 --> 01:05:22,290
Father, please.

1144
01:05:22,290 --> 01:05:24,290
- Daughters-in-law falling out...
- I really don't like Gong Ju Ah.

1145
01:05:24,290 --> 01:05:25,790
- was 100 percent your...
- I can't stand her.

1146
01:05:25,860 --> 01:05:26,960
daughter-in-law's fault.

1147
01:05:27,030 --> 01:05:29,500
So I'm going to set a condition too.
